Last night was passing in and out of consciousness from high fever - tried to take my own temperature but dropped termometer on ground and broke it in the dark, took meds, almost vomited them, fell in powerful state of half-sleep, like a sage/prophet, had a strange revelation

saw Adam and Eve in garden with animals eating/preying on each other, but they were unable to see this, unable to understand lions were killing sheep! but after they ate from Fruit of knowledge of Good and Evil they were able to see it suddenly, realized that it was bad

but nothing had changed, only they had changed, Eden was same as before them. only the way they saw it had changed. then thought came up to me of Sufis who say the ultimate level of holiness is seeing everything as good, seeing Allah in every single thing and action in the world

but I knew there was something deceptive about this all, it was a delusion, some timid form of madness that came upon me - I was shivering in bed, feeling like I might die, I knew the vision was not genuine, it was of demonic origin. I finally fell asleep, now on medicaments DW

It happened when I was in car - I remembered two buildings - one red in North, one green in South - but I was actually mistaken, the red one was in East, the other in West - for a moment all directions mixed up, I felt dizzy, saw buildings on different places, moving - wat mean??

I realize now in daylight how wrong this vision was, how it tries to deny the existence of evil, tries to portray Eden ergo God as fallen - highly blasphemous! Also understand I need antibiotics, am taken care of now, so no worry about me frnds, but do NOT trust visions when sick

It is curious to note that the Lord created the seas before He made greenery - and, logically, plankton and all other microorganisms.

This meant that the primordial ocean was sterile - empty - only moans of the shadows of whales yet unborn echoed under the endless waves.

Can we imagine this unimaginable glory - the raging sea storms, tsunamis falling upon the ocean itself, lighting striking the blank waves...

With no one to witness this but The Trinity Themself, with immeasurable depths of darkness, only the Uncreated Light shining in the world!

I am not a Catholic, but I would fervently support the case for the sainthood of Fr. Alfred Kunz - the priest who was martyred in his own church by satanists.

The holy man was investigating reports of homosexuality and pedophilia in the church and realized a body of satanists...

... had invaded the church and were engaging in demonic rituals involving sodomy and pederasty. Even though he was threatened, he did not give up, and was eventually murdered. I often think of this man. Look at his face, his eyes. Look how pure he is, how joyful! They killed him!

And yet - he died happy, I am sure of it. He knew he died as a martyr, he knew Heaven awaited him, that justice would reign, that it was always meant to be this way.
